-- Merkel: we refuse to accept a Greek bankruptcy
-- 
-- Mon Feb 6, 2012 11:41am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/02/06/us-eurozone-merkel-greece-idUSTRE8151EI20120206

 

 BERLIN  (Reuters) - 801Germany will not accept Greece going bankrupt, Chancellor Angela Merkel said in an interview on Monday. 
 "We refuse to (accept) a Greek bankruptcy. We can't accept that," Merkel told ZDF German TV according to the channel's website. Merkel, in a joint interview with French President Nicolas Sarkozy, also said there would only be a second Greek bailout program if Greece secured the sustainability of its public finances. (Reporting by  Erik Kirschbaum  and  Annika Breidthardt )